abstract: Ten years after diagnosis, could I finally dispense with chemical sleeping aids?
snippet: Ten years after diagnosis, could I finally dispense with chemical sleeping aids?
lead_paragraph: Cancer is a terrible bedfellow. It tosses and turns, snorting and kicking and snatching more than its share of the covers. It never caresses or croons lullabies, but instead hisses innuendos into the wee hours, turning wakefulness into a wake. No wonder insomnia plagues cancer patients, often sending us to chemical aids. Ten years after diagnosis, could I finally dispense with them?

abstract: Appropriately, the first-time feature filmmaker has made a movie about not judging others on appearances: It’s the raucous critical hit “Booksmart.”
snippet: Appropriately, the first-time feature filmmaker has made a movie about not judging others on appearances: It’s the raucous critical hit “Booksmart.”
lead_paragraph: Before Olivia Wilde was a first-time feature director or the star of innumerable projects that she was told would make her the Next Big Thing, she was one more Hollywood newcomer looking for guidance. It was in this unsettled period when Wilde, then around 20, spotted Tilda Swinton at a Golden Globes party, sidled up to her ethereal, chameleonic heroine and awkwardly asked for advice.

headline_main: Olivia Wilde, Director: ‘Too Old to Play Dumb Anymore’

abstract: In her writings and lectures, she postulated that the human race was on the brink of an enhanced way of existing and could bring about great things.
snippet: In her writings and lectures, she postulated that the human race was on the brink of an enhanced way of existing and could bring about great things.
lead_paragraph: The candidate wanted no part of the negativity endemic to politics. Instead she offered an aggressively upbeat view of the future she foresaw for the human race.

abstract: Barring legal challenges, a new Alabama law would effectively outlaw abortions in the state. “This is a war on women,” Senator Kirsten Gillibrand said.
snippet: Barring legal challenges, a new Alabama law would effectively outlaw abortions in the state. “This is a war on women,” Senator Kirsten Gillibrand said.
lead_paragraph: For Senator Elizabeth Warren, the moment brought up memories of “back alley butchers” and “desperate women.” Senator Kamala Harris compared it to “a scene from ‘The Handmaid’s Tale.’” And Senator Kirsten Gillibrand warned about a “war on women,” calling for Americans to “fight like hell.”

abstract: The producers of “Deadwood: The Movie” were able to reunite nearly all of the show’s principal cast. Reassembling the town itself was no less knotty, or crucial.

lead_paragraph: SANTA CLARITA, CALIF. — “Deadwood” is back for one final hello and goodbye.

abstract: Dotdash, once known as About.com, plans to scrap the 85-year-old publication’s print edition and keep most of the editorial staff.
snippet: Dotdash, once known as About.com, plans to scrap the 85-year-old publication’s print edition and keep most of the editorial staff.
lead_paragraph: The courting of Brides magazine had none of the meet-cutes and grand gestures often described in its glossy pages.

abstract: South of Marrakesh, the Draa Valley still exerts an indefinable pull, retaining traces of its now almost-vanished Berber kingdom.
snippet: South of Marrakesh, the Draa Valley still exerts an indefinable pull, retaining traces of its now almost-vanished Berber kingdom.
lead_paragraph: THE SHAMROCK GREEN of Casablanca graded into a flat plain of beige. From the tarmac itself, I could see the beige run into a towering wall of white — the Atlas Mountains. Edith Wharton, in her 1920 travelogue, “In Morocco,” had felt herself fall under the spell of the Atlas and the desert beyond as well. “Unknown Africa,” she writes, “seems much nearer to Morocco than to the white towns of Tunis and the smiling oases of South Algeria. One feels the nearness of Marrakech at Fez, and at Marrakech that of Timbuctoo.”
